Kebbi State has once again positioned itself as the main hub of rice production in the country, with the unveiling of its rice pyramids, which is a pointer to the gains of the Federal Government’s Anchor Borrowers Programme (ABP).
  
The sky-high pyramids does not only signpost the success recorded by the scheme in the last five years, it also reflects the attendant multiplier effects on the economy and the country’s food security.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .